<section id="fs-id1167066864616" class="summary">
<title>Section Summary</title>
<list id="fs-id1167067026948">
<item>Graphs can be used to analyze motion.</item>
<item>The slope of a position vs. time graph is the velocity.</item>
<item>For a straight line graph of position, the slope is the average velocity.</item>
<item>To obtain the instantaneous velocity at a given moment for a curved graph, find the tangent line at that point and take its slope.</item>
</list>
</section>
